  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CSID DID-Network</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective is to ensure the equal participation of persons with disabilities and their organisations in socio-economic activities and community life and contribute to the achievement of the Millennium Development Goals (MDGs) and the United Nations Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities (UNCRPD) in Bangladesh. Its three specific objectives are as follows: Specific objective 1: To strengthen the capacities and voice of DPOs/BPOs and increase their linkages and networking with state and non-state actors; Specific objective 2: To promote the full participation of persons with disabilities in socio-economic activities and improve their access to services; and Specific objective 3: To support local authorities and other government departments to meet their obligations for inclusive development as set out in the United Nations Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities (UNCRPD). These will assist to move towards disability inclusive development. Baseline survey, process documentation, KAP survey, participatory monitoring, community-rooted strategy and operation plan and action research will build evidence. Sustainability will be partly ensured by community resource pool. One component of the project aims to develop standard tools, guidelines, manuals, IEC materials and deliver training to support and explore possible areas of collaboration with academic institutes. The project has a component to support exploring VI &amp; disability accessible ICT. Part of the project implemented by ABC and BVIPS is funded by the EC.</narrative>
  </description>
